'''''Galaxy of Fear: Spore''''' is the ninth book in the young readers ''[[Star Wars: Galaxy of Fear]]'' series.

==Publisher's summary==
''Tash, Zak, and Uncle Hoole stop on the planet Ithor for supplies, including a mineral the Shroud needs for its engines. The mineral isn't available on Ithor, but one of the Ithorians knows where they can find it&mdash;on a mining colony in the middle of a space slug-filled asteroid belt. The journey to the colony is filled with many dangers. But nothing prepares Hoole, Tash, and Zak for what they meet when they reach their destination. An ancient life-form has been released from its tomb. It has lurked there, waiting, for many years. It cannot be seen. It is made from pure evil. And its name is Spore.''

==Plot summary==
Needing raw materials to keep their [[Starship/Legends|starship]] running, [[Mammon Hoole]], [[Tash Arranda/Legends|Tash]] and [[Zak Arranda/Legends|Zak Arranda]] venture into an [[Asteroid field/Legends|asteroid field]] near [[Ithor/Legends|Ithor]], with [[Fandomar Nadon]] as their guide. She is horrified to discover that [[Spore]], an ancient [[Bioweapon/Legends|biological]] threat, has been released from its asteroid [[Tombstone|tomb]]. [[Jerec (Inquisitor)|Jerec]], [[Dark Jedi/Legends|dark servant]] of the [[Palpatine/Legends|Emperor]], wishes to use Spore to give him control of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Empire]]. Spore is a [[Bioengineering/Legends|genetically engineered]] [[Hive mind/Legends|hive-mind]] that can spread its consciousness through its hosts. Tash defeats it by exposing its original host to the vacuum of [[Realspace/Legends|space]].

==Continuity==
[[Fandomar Nadon|Fandomar]] is the wife of [[Momaw Nadon/Legends|Momaw Nadon]], who was featured in ''[[The Sand Tender: The Hammerhead's Tale]]'' ([[1995]]). [[Jerec (Inquisitor)|Jerec]] was the principal villain in the [[1997]] videogame ''[[Star Wars:Jedi Knight: Dark Forces II]]''.<ref name="TERC" />

